post_title: Does Half and Half stay fresh forever, even when not refrigerated (the ones in the little plastic cups)?

======================================================

(You): Does Half and Half stay fresh forever, even when not refrigerated (the ones in the little plastic cups)?

(Anh): Good until the container breaks down and allows air in.

(You): thanks. Why can't they store regular milk in airtight containers and not require refrigeration?

----------------------

(A.J.): Most (if not all) non-refrigerated, 'plastic cup' creamers are non-dairy.  Because of sugars and fats present in true half-half, it will spoil more quickly if unrefrigerated.

----------------------

(Kathy): They always need to be refrigerated. The only creamer that can live outside the cold is the powdered kind.

