(You): thanks! I sort of knew they could be stored outside the fridge, but I guess my question was: for how long? Like, can I buy an years worth in bulk and keep it w/o worrying it'll go bad?

----------------------

(Patti): Absolutely not. I've had those curdle in my coffee before. It definitely has a shelf life. It lasts a lot longer than regular milk because of the high fat content, but it will still go off eventually. If you want to keep them usable for an extended period of time, they can be frozen.

(You): thanks! So keep a quantity frozen and a quantity thawed for immediate use?

(Patti): Yep. Though they'd probably thaw very quickly, so you wouldn't need to get them out of the freezer more than half an hour before using. You might even experiment with putting a frozen one straight into your coffee...I suspect it might work (but not 100% sure). Can't hurt to try it!

